Basic Definition of Probability
The probability of an event is equal to the:


Number of favourable outcomes / Number of unfavourable outcomes

Number of unfavourable outcomes / Number of total outcomes

Number of favourable outcomes / Number of total outcomes
Feedback :
Yes, this is the basic definition of probability.
Correct

Number of total outcomes / Number of favourable outcomes

Questions:2/6
 
 
 
 
 
 
Basic Definition of Probability
A regular die is thrown. The probability of getting the number 5 is:


5 / 6

1 / 6
Feedback :
Number of favourable outcomes = 1 (i.e. the outcome that the die throws 5). Total number of outcomes = 6 (The die could throw 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 or 6). Probability = Number of favourable outcomes / Total number of outcomes = 1 / 6.
Correct

1 / 3

1 / 2

