Questions:1/7
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Advanced Concepts in Probability
A regular die is thrown. The probability of getting the number 4 or 5 in this throw is:


0

1 / 6

1 / 3
Feedback :
Define X as the number achieved after throwing the die. You know that P(X = 4) = 1 / 6 and P(X = 5) = 1 / 6. Now, using addition rule of probability, you will get that P(X = 4 or 5) = P(X = 4) + P(X = 5) = 1 / 6 + 1 / 6 = 1 / 3.
Correct

1 / 2

Questions:2/7
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Advanced Concepts in Probability
A regular die is thrown. The probability of getting the number 4 and 5 in this throw is:


0
Feedback :
It is impossible to get two numbers in one throw of the die.
Correct

1 / 6

1 / 3

1 / 2 


Questions:3/7
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Advanced Concepts in Probability
A regular die is thrown. The probability of getting the number 4 in the first throw and 5 in the second throw is:


2 / 6

1 / 36
Feedback :
Again, P(getting the number 4) = 1 / 6 and P(getting the number 5) = 1 / 6. Now, using multiplication rule, you get that P(getting the number 4 in the 1st trial AND the number 5 in the 2nd trial) = P(getting the number 4 in the 1st trial)*P(getting the number 5 in the second trial) = 1 / 6 * 1 / 6 = 1 / 36.
Correct

20 / 36

9 / 36

Questions:4/7
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Advanced Concepts in Probability
A fair coin is tossed. The probability of getting a head or a tail is?


1
Feedback :
P(heads) = 0.5, P(tails) = 0.5, Using addition rule, you have P(heads OR tails) = 0.5 + 0.5 = 1.
Correct

0.25

0.5

0


