Questions:6/7
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Advanced Concepts in Probability
A fair coin is tossed. The probability of getting a head in the 1st toss and a tail in the 2nd toss is?


1

0.25
Feedback :
P(heads) = 0.5, P(tails) = 0.5, Using multiplication rule, you have P(heads in 1st toss AND tails in 2nd toss) = P(heads in 1st toss)*P(tails in 2nd toss) = 0.5*0.5 = 0.25.
Correct

0.5

0


