Power Law
Please Note: This is an additional resource. The link for this session has been integrated at an appropriate place in the main EDA module.

 

You learnt that many data sets follow the phenomenon of power law. There are many real-life examples where you may find power laws being followed, such as frequency of earthquakes vs intensity of earthquakes, number of people with an income vs the income itself, etc.

 

Let us understand what causes power law.

https://www.investopedia.com/updates/enron-scandal-summary/


